The Government District 
This section of the cavern system seems to dwarf the rest with a ceiling
extending nearly twice as high as the previous branches. Stalactites and
stalagmites have been carefully carved away from this area giving it a groomed
and almost artistic appearance, a smooth archway dug into the southern wall
adding compliment. Inside the archway is a thick set of durasteel blastdoors
which add a flash of modern architecture. The symbol of the Rylothian
government has been meticulously etched into each door and an advanced
voice-recognition system has been placed on the right-hand side of the
entrance. The air here is lighter on the lungs, the moisture being dried out by
a massive dehumidification system emplaced on the westernmost wall. Heavily
fortified and expertly  crafted, this appears to be the entrance to an area of
importance.
Obvious exits:
North - Too dark to tell
East  - Too dark to tell
South - Kala'uun Capital Building [Rotunda]
West  - Too dark to tell

Kala'uun Capital Building [Rotunda] 
An impressive sight to behold, this area of the cave system has been carved
into a colossal dome of sorts, with the smoothed ceiling spanning over 100
meters from edge to edge. Ancient tribal cave paintings have been transferred
from all over the planet, restored, and put on display in this awe inspiring
central passage. This area serves a double purpose as both a  museum displaying
important Twi'lek history, as well as a hub for travel within the government
building. A careful observer could spend days studying the imagery here,
assuming the hustle  and bustle of the government workers didn't disturb them.
This area seems to be occupied with  heavy traffic at nearly all hours of the
day as officials travel from wing-to-wing of this facility. 
Obvious exits:
North - Too dark to tell
East  - Kala'uun Capital Building [Main Corridor]
South - Kala'uun Capital Building [Rotunda]
